Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.32,0:21:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for five years wondering what to do with it you have access to all the\Ninformation that exists now or ever within one second takes that long to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.20,0:21:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,discover any secret in the universe so you can see why I walked around for five\Nyears thinking what to do with this first of all it's best not to tell
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.76,0:22:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody yes so it is an incredible gift it's an incredible gift mankind has\Nsuffered untold agonies for centuries and centuries for a lack of the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.28,0:22:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,knowledge of the difference between truth and falsehood to not know that\Nthere's any truth and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.07,0:22:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,falsehood condemns mankind in this war's poverty savagery's sickness agony\Nsuffering and death the affliction that is one has been one of ignorance all the
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.76,0:22:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,great avatars buddha christ krishna all say there is only one sin only one\Nproblem and that is ignorance ignorance but man had no way of discerning truth
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.41,0:22:44.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and falsehood\Nyou
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.79,0:22:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,can find it anywhere except God is God is sent and the such thing we起來\Nto be the acknowledge and acknowledge it and if the Buddha step back and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.65,0:23:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,annihilate answer of 50 was in fact a promotion each of us has a cooking\Nation lining and just all you have to do isgruppe this area which began you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.56,0:23:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can儘 appear their lord better so it will 어제 do that or disagree\Nphase two is you will all act according to the grace of the teacher we take in
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.18,0:23:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness and we simply hate or be uncertain that the you will I will not\Naccept if you are not devoid of this principle yet even the words of the great spiritual teachers words the great spiritual teachers now we have at hand a gift which to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.58,0:23:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and it jumped to 205.\NTherefore, mankind throughout the centuries
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.05,0:23:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,has been dominated collectively by a consciousness\Nthat was below truth, non-integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.29,0:23:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see a civilization in history\Nwhich grew with an overall collective consciousness level of 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.30,0:23:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly in the late 1980s, around 87,\Nat about the time of the harmonic concordance,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.98,0:23:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but not caused by it, it jumped to 205.\NPeople speak of the second coming of Christ,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.30,0:24:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and they think it's going to be somebody\Nwho suddenly gets born in Brooklyn and appears on television.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.48,0:24:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a rather naive understanding.\NThe Christ, then, is a conscious awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.39,0:24:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, when the consciousness level of mankind went over 200,\Nthat, to me, was the return of the consciousness of the Christ
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.21,0:24:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which now...\Ndominates mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.05,0:24:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The collective level again went up last November,\Nfrom 205 to 207.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.81,0:24:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, we now live in a different world.\NAnd as you can see by the daily newspaper,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.48,0:24:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,truth often brings...\NPeople think truth is going to bring peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.11,0:24:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,People call themselves spiritual,\Npicture that it's all flowers and hymns,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.61,0:24:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and saintly smiles.\NChrist said,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.15,0:25:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I came with a sword, a sword of truth, right?\NBecause when consciousness level is 190,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.38,0:25:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a world in which,\Nslipping you a few bucks,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.44,0:25:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,you can even buy the UN,\N42 billion dollars,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.99,0:25:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you can buy the UN Security Council.\NWhat happens when consciousness level reaches 205?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.44,0:25:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That's no longer okay.\NWhen it reaches 207, it's very much not okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.36,0:25:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Very much not okay.\NIt used to be, success was fame, fortune, money, wealth, fancy cars, Cadillacs, a yacht.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.18,0:25:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the new success is integrity.\NAnybody can have those things.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.04,0:25:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Back east where I lived, everybody had them.\NEverybody was a multimillionaire.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.98,0:26:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I belonged to, everybody was a millionaire.\NEverybody had a yacht.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.08,0:26:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody.\NEverybody had six Cadillacs and servants.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.55,0:26:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Did me a thing.\NMost of them inherited it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.32,0:26:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the best way to do it, folks.\NNo, I wouldn't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.78,0:26:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you inherit it, it really isn't yours.\NIt's really not what you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.20,0:26:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're all sort of apologetic for it.\NSo you play polo or something, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.22,0:26:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Go to the right school and all.\NNo, 207 then, there's quite a push.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.46,0:26:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a push for integrity.\NSo what you see is unrest in society, contention, conflict, social discord, because the energies
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.54,0:27:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200 now are in a world which calibrates at 207.\NSo pure rhetoric alone will not cut the ice anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.63,0:27:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got to be backed up by some facts.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.79,0:27:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,A new paradigm then of social acceptance.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.79,0:27:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So social acceptance, integrity.\NI could have saved Martha, trip to jail, easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.79,0:27:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Martha, go to a 12 step meeting.\N10th step is when we were wrong, we promptly admitted it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.04,0:27:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,All she had to do is say, well, look, if your stockbroker said he's thinking that something's\Nbottoming out, wouldn't you sell it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.04,0:27:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I would too.\NSo I'd fine her, you know, $50,000 and end the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.00,0:27:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Big deal.\NSo, but no, she's really in prison for lack of integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.04,0:27:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the thing.\NShe's a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.04,0:27:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a person.\NShe's a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.54,0:27:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a person.\NShe's a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.54,0:27:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a person.\NShe's a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.54,0:27:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a person.\NShe's a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.54,0:27:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a person.\NShe's a person.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.47,0:27:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's really, she was convicted of lack of integrity.\NWhen you lie to a federal jury, you know, that's why she's in jail.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.32,0:27:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Not for money.\NNot for wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.64,0:28:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Not for fame.\NYou see at 207, you go to prison for lack of integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.99,0:28:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow.\NIt's a new paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.99,0:28:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, in the old days, you could have bought off everybody, and she wouldn't be here.\NNow, it's not so easy to buy everybody off.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.31,0:28:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see now a strange interface between the old culture.\NUh.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.07,0:28:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,. .\Nat 190, and then interacting with the culture at 205 and 207, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.00,0:28:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's like you, you know.\NAll right, so the advance of truth doesn't necessarily bring tranquil waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.64,0:28:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it may disturb things for a period of time.\NAnd people who have gotten involved in intense spiritual work,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.81,0:28:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,before they get there, they think it's going to be hearts and flowers\Nand we're all going to sing hymns.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.25,0:28:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll dance around the maypole and have peace marches, peace vigils,\Nand that will bring about peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.03,0:29:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you find that it's quite the contrary, that you now have a new paradigm\Nand reflected in this new paradigm is the downside of the old,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.25,0:29:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and so you have a conflict, a conflict going on.\NWe'll have peace, all right, but it may take a few thousand years, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.28,0:29:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No point to being impatient.\NTo merely know that all things are happening in and of their own
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.60,0:29:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,with no external cause, because the difficulty in a group such as is here today\Nis a group like this is stuck in the Newtonian paradigm of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.14,0:29:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The Newtonian paradigm is that there is a this causing a that.\NIt's dualistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.80,0:30:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also the very source of thinking that there is a separate individuality\Nand a separate individual eye, a separate personal eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.15,0:30:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no separate personal eye talking here, going.\NThe field, the field, the presence, because of the audience,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.73,0:30:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,speaks back to itself as it speaks, and I don't have anything to do with it.\NNothing to do with what is being said, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.58,0:30:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.\NThat happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.23,0:30:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Many years ago, when the personal self, the infinite presence is so powerful\Nthat it really extinguishes anything that is not itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.10,0:30:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And the personal self became disappeared and the mind became silent.\NThe side, the mind right now is still silent.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.88,0:31:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I listened to the mind, said nothing at all.\NNeither does yours, but you think it does, and that's the difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.69,0:31:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we'll start out where to make that jump, you see, and then we'll go back to the lecture.\NThe mind thinks there is a you, and this you is causing this sequence of events, sequential causality.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.67,0:31:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw through that in theology class.\NI went to a Jesuit university.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.28,0:31:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The arguments for the presence of God is that there must be a great big capital A back here.\NWhich in itself is fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.52,0:32:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an idiotic thing, and at the time I was an atheist, and it's a stupid remark.\NAnyway, a sequence arises from that which is not of the sequence, not of the sequence, not of the sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.23,0:32:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the average person thinks there is a personal me, and it is causing these thoughts or actions in a chain reaction.\NCausality is.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.48,0:32:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This causing of that.\NTherefore, there must be an entity causing all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.12,0:32:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a presumption.\NThe mind can't understand infinity, so it presumes that in the sequence of events there would be a prime cause of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.79,0:32:43.79,Default,,0,0,0,,God must have a prime cause of something.\NThat which always has been obviously needs no cause.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.79,0:32:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond cause.\NThis is where the thoughts are, and this is where there is a teaching, a mistranslation of the teaching of the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.04,0:33:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That the infinite reality, enlightenment, is seeing between two thoughts.\NIn the seeming nothingness and void.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.36,0:33:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, many of us spent years and years cross-legged, breathing in strange places, wearing sandals, incense, the whole.\NLooking for the space between A, B, and C.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.03,0:33:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Did anybody here ever find it?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.65,0:33:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe somebody says yes.\NYou know, you're a liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.65,0:33:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it cannot be found between the thoughts.\NThat's a mistranslation of the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.65,0:33:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But, endless lifetimes have been spent.\NNico and I are experts at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.80,0:33:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We spent lifetimes as Hinayana monks.\NPathway of negation, not this, not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.12,0:33:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, between.\NYou cannot catch the infinite space between thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.18,0:34:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the mind is what's looking for the space between two thoughts.\NAnd the mind cannot catch something that happens in less than one ten-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.17,0:34:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is limited to one ten-thousandth of a second.\NSo, the mind is unable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.62,0:34:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What's today's lecture's name?\NObserving and witnessing.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.68,0:34:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind, as we will see later, can't move fast enough to catch it between two thoughts.\NIt's got to be faster than one ten-thousandth of a second to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.68,0:34:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And it can't.\NThe mind cannot move faster than one ten-thousandth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.80,0:34:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, when a rabbit runs across the road, you put the brake on.\NIf you're quick and honest, you'll see that it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.97,0:35:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, the personal self congratulates itself that I stepped on the brake.\NNow, it already braked.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.48,0:35:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the I, in one ten-thousandth of a second, claims authorship.\NThat's the difference between enlightenment and non-enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.93,0:35:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's in that one ten-thousandth of a second.\NI had the good fortune when I was very young that I caught the ego doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.57,0:35:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I caught it.\NIt had already saved the rabbit's life and braked.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.40,0:35:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I caught the ego.\NI caught it claiming credit.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.40,0:35:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But I knew it had already happened.\NAt the moment it said, I, the phenomena had already occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.17,0:35:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that was fortuitous.\NAt that young age, I didn't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.49,0:35:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't understand the implication of that.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.74,0:35:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you cannot find the infinite reality between the thoughts,\Nthen where is the infinite reality?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.90,0:36:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And here is where it is here.\NBeneath all the thinkingness is silence, void, silence.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.17,0:36:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of thinkingness, then, is an infinite silence and infinite peace.\NAnd if you go in there, it's hard to lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.17,0:36:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm not going to go in there now.\NBecause you feel weak and you begin to weep and you want to leave the world as soon as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.06,0:36:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay out of there.\NSo, anyway, it's the infinite silent field out of which your consciousness and your thinkingness is arising.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.54,0:36:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So, your thoughts are not arising this way.\NEach one is being individually created sequentially.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.54,0:36:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,See there?\NOops.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.83,0:37:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one is being independently sequentially.\NSo, instead of like billiard balls, thoughts are really like flying fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.28,0:37:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember World War II, we were in something or other sea.\NAnd I don't remember what sea it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.83,0:37:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, flying fish are flying out and landing on the deck.\NSo, a flying fish arises here.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.86,0:37:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All of a sudden, over here, another flying fish comes up.\NOver here, another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.86,0:37:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Another one comes up.\NEach one is coming up separately individually.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.86,0:37:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Of its own nature.\NSpontaneously emerging of its own nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.17,0:37:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because its nature, as a flying fish, is to do that.\NNobody is forcing it to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.42,0:37:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody is causing it to do it.\NThe nature of the flying fish is it gets a kick out of doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.45,0:38:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you'll see how sick and weird the human mind is.\NThis fish comes up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.80,0:38:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This fish comes up here.\NThis fish comes up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.80,0:38:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And some idiot who's always a professor at some university.\NThey're always a professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.28,0:38:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Will tell you that the fish are triangulating.\NThere's always this incredible mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.32,0:38:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to go through all the formulas and crap.\NDemonstrates the triangulation of fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.96,0:38:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what your mind does.\NSo, your mind is the idiot scientist.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.96,0:38:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The idiot professor.\NSo, standing in your way is not ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.02,0:38:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NIt's the idiot professor.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.63,0:38:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The fish doesn't.\NThe fish just is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.72,0:39:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NEach one of us just is what we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.97,0:39:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not caused by anything at all.\NThere's no cause for anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.52,0:39:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Creation is the unfolding of the unmanifest becoming manifest.\NThe infinite potentiality becoming manifest.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.45,0:39:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This is by virtue of the incredible power of the field.\NThat explains and now we understand how karma works.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.99,0:39:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, each one of us are karmic inheritance.\NWhich is sort of like a software program.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.62,0:39:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all born with a software program.\NThe brain is your hardware.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.78,0:39:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's genetically engineered.\NYou've got nothing to do with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.61,0:39:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're born with consciousness.\NSo, you're born with this software programming.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.61,0:40:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Software.\NThat's your karmic inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.09,0:40:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That defines who you are.\NYour calibrated level.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.28,0:40:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody has a calibrated level of consciousness at the moment they're born.\NThe moment you're born, you already have a calibratable level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.28,0:40:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Without karma, how would you explain such a phenomena?\NThis now plays.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.38,0:40:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the hardware of the brain plays any software you put on it.\NSo, the karma is your software.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.38,0:40:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The karmic inheritance.\NAll the decisions made through great eons of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.56,0:40:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, because of the software, you might say you're like an iron filing.\NEvery spiritual decision then tends to change the configuration.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.36,0:40:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say you've got a little karmic body.\NIt looks like caramel taffy or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.36,0:41:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,All the decisions you've made have positioned it to be the way it is.\NNow, in an infinite power, in an infinite field, like an electromagnetic field,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.23,0:41:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,this little iron filing is positioned as a consequence of the power of the field.\NThe field is so infinitely powerful that as a little iron filing,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.12,0:41:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,you automatically go to where you fit in the field.\NAs a consequence of that which you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.27,0:41:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the power of the field determines all phenomena.\NWhen and where you're born, how long you live.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.00,0:41:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And we discovered also through karmic research, through kinesiologic research,\Nyou have a calibrated level of consciousness at birth.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.44,0:42:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,People who are born are calibrated at 40.\N60, 80, 200, 300, 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.94,0:42:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, at the moment of birth, the time of death is already preset.\NIs that fatalism?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.90,0:42:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NYou can call it whatever you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.90,0:42:23.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact is you enter already with a certain level of potential,\Nconsciousness potential.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.12,0:42:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And your exit is already prearranged.\NSo you don't have to worry about dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.92,0:42:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all handled.\NYou know, the scary thing about this world is not...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.54,0:42:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The scary thing is how do you get out of here?\NThey keep closing all the doors, curing all these illnesses, safety features.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.54,0:42:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you can't get out of this place.\NWe're trapped. How are you going to get out of this place, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.54,0:42:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting here is easy. Getting out of here, how are you going to get out?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.37,0:43:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to get an exit permit from the government.\NSo that's not predestination, which is something else altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.35,0:43:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But\Nyour time is limited and the time of leaving is already preset.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.35,0:43:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sort of like getting a...\NWhat do you call a computer disc now with a movie on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.60,0:43:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,DVD? What do you call them?\NDVD, yes. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.73,0:43:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,When you buy a DVD, the end of the sturdy is already in the tape\Nor the disc, what do you call it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.73,0:43:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The end of the sturdy is already there.\NThe fact that it hasn't unrolled yet doesn't mean it's not there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.24,0:43:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's like you're born with this computer disc CDD thing in your head.\NThis karmic CDB? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.56,0:43:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,DVD.\NHuh? DVD. DVD.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.11,0:44:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're born with a karmic DVD.\NHowever, you can play it on your computer and you can change the story as it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.80,0:44:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But when the end of the disc arrives, that's the end of the disc, folks.\NAnd if you listen to what we say in the lectures,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.94,0:44:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you will be very, very happy about it.\NYou can go now, you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.44,0:44:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Lord.\NIt's okay to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.34,0:44:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I had a huge psychiatric practice for many years\Nand even after retirement, they didn't have anybody to go to the nursing homes
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.50,0:44:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and various places.\NSo in the county, I used to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.50,0:45:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,30,000 miles a year, running around doing nursing homes and all.\NEvery nursing home always has an old crone strapped in a wheelchair.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.08,0:45:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She's got all these tubes, pipes hanging down there,\Nall these devices, machines, computerized stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.88,0:45:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and she's always going,\NHelp! Help! Help! Help! Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.94,0:45:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, Doctor, Doctor, can't you do something?\NShe keeps, Help! Help! Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.94,0:45:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Help! Help! Help!\NI know what she wants, but it's illegal.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.35,0:45:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Help me get out of here.\NHelp me get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.40,0:45:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They won't let me out of here.\NYou cannot leave this world without Medicare permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.52,0:46:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Medicare breaks. It's not permissible.\NPull all these tubes and things out.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.68,0:46:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what she wants.\NShe keeps trying to pull the tube out, you know, because she wants to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.68,0:46:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So what do they do? They strap her arm down. Literally.\NTie down their arm so you can't croak.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.07,0:46:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And get the hell out of here.\NBefore things get worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.62,0:46:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so you come in with this karmic program,\Nyou know, your software.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.02,0:46:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got already a calibratable level of consciousness at the moment of birth.\NThe level of consciousness will determine what kinds of choices and options
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.60,0:46:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you will have to make decisions about.\NAlso, everyone is born under the most karmically optimal conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.42,0:46:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,for their evolution and growth.\NThat was a major discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.42,0:47:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's a fact.\NEverybody knows Susan, but I want to make sure everybody knows Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.96,0:47:18.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Without whom, we wouldn't know anything.\NOkay, so the moment of...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.18,0:47:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What did we ask?\NThe moment of death is only a percent?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.53,0:47:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. No, it was karmic potential.\NOh, yes. Everyone's...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.63,0:47:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The circumstances of your birth\Nare perfectly aligned with your karmic potential
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.63,0:47:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to potentiate your evolution and growth.\NWe have permission to ask, that will learn.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.63,0:47:51.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And the answer to that is true.\NResist. True.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.33,0:47:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That gets rid of self-pity, folks.\NPoor me.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.43,0:48:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The competition for being a victim in the poor me\Nis so severe in society.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.84,0:48:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, if you get to be more awful and pathetic than somebody else,\Nthey just...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.84,0:48:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They're so full of envy and hatred.\NThey just hate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.00,0:48:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,My condition is worse than your condition.\NBeing the martyr, the victim of injustice,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.69,0:48:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is the keynote to American society today.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.79,0:48:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So realizing that whatever the circumstances of your birth were,\Nhardship, illnesses, death of parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.01,0:48:45.49,Default,,0,0,0,,sexual predation, anything,\Nis part of one's karmic inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.10,0:48:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Karma has its upside.\NIt also has the necessity for the undoing
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.90,0:48:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of things, the undoing of things.\NSo if we accept the less pleasant things about our life
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.93,0:49:09.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and get that it's an undoing, an undoing,\Nand therefore to be grateful for it,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.37,0:49:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,somehow, when you reach a certain level of consciousness,\Nthen you remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.40,0:49:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You remember what the events were in previous life,\Nin a prior life, what the world would call a prior life.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.40,0:49:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all one life, but prior incarnation.\NThat which is infinite in dimension can only have a beginning and an ending.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.56,0:49:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So your consciousness has always been.\NThe field out of which your consciousness arises
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.40,0:49:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,has always been.\NAnd because it has always been,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.14,0:49:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,it will always be.\NDeath is not a possibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.14,0:50:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad.\NNot the people that dashes your final hopes, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.14,0:50:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you have to accept responsibility.\NDeath is just, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.14,0:50:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it's long for a cop-out, a cop-out.\NNo, you can't cop-out with physical death.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.14,0:50:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you didn't undo it all,\Nyou come back again until you undo it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.14,0:50:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, the vicissitudes of life\Nwe can look at from wisdom and say,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.62,0:50:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what it's serving right now,\Nbut obviously it is serving something,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.62,0:50:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,either individually or collectively,\Nbecause people also have collective karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.62,0:50:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah? Collective karma.\N10,000 people kill 50,000 innocent civilians.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.00,0:50:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how do you undo that?\NHow do the Vikings undo butchering
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.90,0:50:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,tens of thousands of innocent civilians?\NLittle babies in their crib.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.90,0:51:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you undo that?\NIf you want to get to heaven,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.32,0:51:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to have to undo it.\NSo, you need an opportunity to undo it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.32,0:51:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, karma prepares the infinite possibility.\NTherefore, we all inherit now,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.73,0:51:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of this life,\Ntherefore, is a gift,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.73,0:51:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because through this life,\Nwe can undo that which was negative and a deterrent,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.76,0:51:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and we can align ourself with that which is integrous.\NThe only difficulty is that the world has never known
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.04,0:51:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,truth and falsehood and what is integrous.\NThat's difficult, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.04,0:51:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to live a life without a compass.\NYou only have the say-so of tradition and religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.04,0:51:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, traditional religion told you which way is truth.\NSo, we need the...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.08,0:51:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want to call it? Number one.\NNumber one or number uno.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.08,0:51:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you call that thing? Slide.\NSlide.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.71,0:52:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Slide. Ta-dum!\NThey've become relatively well-known.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.22,0:52:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The map of consciousness.\NThese are the levels of man throughout all of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.22,0:52:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,as recorded throughout all of time.\NDifferent wording and different cultures,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.25,0:52:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but they always boil down to exactly the same thing.\NExactly the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.25,0:52:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And we call these the levels of consciousness.\NYou can calibrate their relative energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.57,0:52:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And...\NUm...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.02,0:52:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In doing this, the numbers became so large,\NI had to switch to logarithmic.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.28,0:52:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Logarithmic.\NSo, each of these numbers are 10 to that power.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:47.16,0:52:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This is 10 times 10 times 10.\N250 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.16,0:52:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,10 times 10 times 10 times 10.\NYou do that 250 times.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.16,0:53:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You see that's a pretty big number.\NSo, it wouldn't fit on the blackboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.16,0:53:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we went to logarithmic.\NWe discovered that anything that ever existed, now or ever,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.20,0:53:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it can be calibrated on a scale of one to a thousand.\NWe said, what's the highest consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.28,0:53:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that's ever walked this world?\NAnd we got the great avatars.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.28,0:53:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus Christ, Buddha, Krishna, Zoroaster.\NIs the infinite...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.08,0:53:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the top potential.\NThe reasons for it are not important.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.30,0:53:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But, frankly, it's because of the nature\Nof protoplasm and the central nervous system
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.30,0:53:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,can only handle up to a power.\NSee, because you're talking logarithmically now,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.30,0:53:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,as frequencies, energies go up,\Nthe frequency gets higher and higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.30,0:53:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The human nervous system, frankly,\Nhas great difficulty handling anything
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.30,0:54:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,over maybe 750.\NFrom 750 up, you really should be in a different dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.54,0:54:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,From one to a thousand, we discovered then\Nthat we could calibrate the consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.54,0:54:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of anything on earth.\NEverything, now or ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.54,0:54:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And we discovered, as I said, the kinesiologic test.\NWhen I saw Diamond do it, I realized it was...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.80,0:54:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is like a giant electrostatic field.\NRemember on the electrostatic speakers?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.80,0:54:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a membrane, electrostatically charged membrane.\NNow, when you bring a charge up to it,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.80,0:54:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,it reacts with an equal and opposite reaction.\NIf you bring up...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.05,0:54:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you who know physics will laugh at this.\NLet's say we bring up 32 frequencies.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.44,0:54:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Three protons and 32 neutrons,\Nor what do you call them?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.44,0:54:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Negatrons.\NElectrons.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.78,0:54:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And protons.\NWhatever they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.61,0:54:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever the field holds,\Nan equal and opposite reaction shows up.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.61,0:55:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in the presence of truth then,\Nconsciousness recognizes...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.50,0:55:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The difference between truth and falsehood,\Nand it recognizes the electrostatic charge,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.50,0:55:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you might say.\NThe higher truth goes up,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.50,0:55:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,the higher and more powerful its charge.\NSo, when we calibrate something,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.85,0:55:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I hold it silently in mind.\NPeople say, you're suggesting...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.92,0:55:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget, kinesiology has been examined,\Nyou know, for decades by thousands of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.92,0:55:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So, every argument you can think of\Nhas already been looked at by thousands of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.92,0:55:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't influence what she's thinking\Nbecause I don't tell her what I'm thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.30,0:55:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We only verbalize it when we have an audience.\NIf I want to know something,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.56,0:55:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to spend the time and energy\Ntalking about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.56,0:55:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Once in a while she'll say, what was that?\NWhat was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.88,0:56:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThere's one I haven't had a chance to ask yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.25,0:56:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask that.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.25,0:56:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm thinking calibrates over 200 resistances.\N300.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.66,0:56:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,250.\N260.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.30,0:56:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm holding in mind is a phenomenon.\N250.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.30,0:56:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,260.\NTelepathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.30,0:56:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We never did calibrate telepathy.\NIt says 250.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.00,0:56:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, obviously, she didn't know what I was thinking\Nbecause I've had it on my disk for a couple of months.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.00,0:56:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Someday I'll ask.\NTelepathy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.00,0:56:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We never did ask it.\NA lot of people have experienced it on various levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.48,0:56:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,People who go for silent weekends\Nvery often
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.48,0:56:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,become very adept at it.\NI went on a...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.86,0:56:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was only a four or five day silent retreat,\Nand within 24 hours
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.92,0:56:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody was telepathic.\NYou wouldn't even think butter.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.92,0:57:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You would sit down\Nand somebody would just hand you butter
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.92,0:57:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,like they knew it.\NSome of our staff have recently been
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.63,0:57:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,on silent weekends\Nand they say it's sort of magical and mystical.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.63,0:57:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So you discover that telepathic capacity.\NIt's not that you're consciously thinking a thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.63,0:57:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,but what you're holding in mind\Neven non-verbally
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.63,0:57:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is somehow knowable by other people.\NAnyway, 250, that's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.63,0:57:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is the way we do it.\NI don't want to influence her in any way.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.63,0:57:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,She's so sophisticated\Nand skilled at this over the years
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.88,0:57:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that it doesn't influence her.\NBut just to make sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.88,0:57:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no idea what was going to come up\Nabout telepathy myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.88,0:57:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So we discovered\Nyou can calibrate everything
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.10,0:57:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,on a scale of consciousness\Nthat goes from one to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.10,0:57:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The critical level,\Nand I forgot my pointer today,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.20,0:57:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I always take it where I don't need it\Nand forget it where I need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.20,0:57:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We found that\Neverything that is true
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.96,0:58:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrates 200 and up,\Nand below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.83,0:58:08.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So then we,\Nbecause having been a psychiatrist,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.83,0:58:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,psychoanalyst, etc.,\Nwe naturally calibrated these things
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.83,0:58:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,according to the\Nclassical levels
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.86,0:58:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of human consciousness.\NEach level then
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.04,0:58:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,has its own way of\Nunderstanding or perceiving God,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.52,0:58:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,including atheists.\NAtheists can be predicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.87,0:58:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Their view of themself,\Na person's opinion of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.56,0:58:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We give this level\Na name
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.27,0:58:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,that's common and familiar\Nso everybody knows
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.27,0:58:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,what grief is,\Neverybody knows what shame is.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.81,0:58:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have the emotion\Nthat goes with it, emotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.81,0:58:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you see\Nevery day's headlines.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.81,0:59:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Every night's news broadcast.\NYou can calibrate
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.81,0:59:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,everything that happens on the news.\NAnd this is the process
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.81,0:59:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,going on in consciousness\Non the far right.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.93,0:59:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This plus knowing how to do kinesiology\Ncan give you an answer
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.93,0:59:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,to anything.\NRight now,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.05,0:59:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind in a way has\Nthe most incredible gift
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.60,0:59:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,it's ever received.\NFirst of all, the revelation
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.60,0:59:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of the great teachers in history.\NThe gift of how to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.62,0:59:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This world,\Nand this is hard to get,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.45,0:59:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,does not know truth from falsehood.\NThis world does not know
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.35,0:59:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,truth from falsehood,\Nnor does it have any test or capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.35,0:59:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to differentiate the two.\NConvincingness has nothing to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.75,1:00:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The most convincing, persuasive\Npoliticians in history
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.03,1:00:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,have led mankind\Nto death by the tens of millions
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.09,1:00:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in my lifetime,\Ntens of millions
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.09,1:00:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,died as a result of the\Nrhetorical,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.67,1:00:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,oratorical excellence of Adolf Hitler,\NStalin,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.08,1:00:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Milosevic,\Nthe fallacy of Marxism,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.67,1:00:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,etc.\NThe human mind
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.24,1:00:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so, by the tens of millions\Npeople salute
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.24,1:00:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and worship falsehood.\NSalute and worship
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.44,1:00:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,leaders who calibrate at 50.\NGive up their lives
Dialogue: 0,1:00:50.01,1:00:54.01,Default,,0,0,0,,for leaders who calibrate at 50\Nworse than
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.01,1:00:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Machine Gun Kelly.\NWorse than Machine Gun Kelly.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.61,1:01:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Lower than Machine Gun Kelly.\NPeople give up their lives
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.61,1:01:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,for them.\NDonate all their properties.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.61,1:01:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Sacrifice their children.\NSend their sons off to war.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.61,1:01:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,To fight for illusion.\NSo really this is
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.53,1:01:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the greatest gifts mankind\Nhas ever really received.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.53,1:01:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only dawned on me more and more recently.\NWhat an incredible
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.98,1:01:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it's probably the most\Nvaluable
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.98,1:01:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,gift we own right now.\NJust think what you could do
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.23,1:01:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,if you could know truth from\Nfalsehood about anything,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.23,1:01:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,anytime.\NHow would it make your life different?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.96,1:01:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The only requirement\Nto get an honest answer
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.31,1:01:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is that you have to\Nyourself be aligned
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.50,1:01:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and committed to integrity\Nand truth. That eliminates
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.53,1:02:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,85%\Nof the world's population.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.52,1:02:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, what we're talking about\Ntoday is accessible
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.04,1:02:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to only 15% of the world's\Npopulation. It calibrates
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.04,1:02:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,over 200. If the purpose\Nof asking the question is personal
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.15,1:02:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,selfishness, then the answer\Nis unreliable.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.47,1:02:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,When you ask for something, people say\Ncan I use kinesiology about my
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.47,1:02:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,business? Yes.\NSo long as you ask only in the name of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.47,1:02:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,the highest good. Anything\Nin reference to your personal life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.47,1:02:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say it is in\Nthe highest good. The highest good
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.47,1:02:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning for the world,\Nfor society, for your employees,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.47,1:02:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,for your employees and their families.\NFor the good and welfare
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.47,1:02:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,after all, everyone\Nwho has any kind of money is now
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.53,1:02:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the steward of that money.\NSo you now have like a moral responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:53.53,1:02:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you have money, you have in a way\Na certain moral responsibility
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.53,1:03:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to be a responsible steward for that money.\NThe taxpayers have worked
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.53,1:03:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,hard for that money.\NWe expect our public
Dialogue: 0,1:03:05.60,1:03:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,officials to\Nbe considerate of that. We've all
Dialogue: 0,1:03:09.63,1:03:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,busted our chops for that\Nmoney.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.59,1:03:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So if\Nthe intention of the question is
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.59,1:03:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous and you yourself calibrate over\N200, then the reliability
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.59,1:03:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,should be excellent and it's like riding\Na bicycle, you just need a little experience
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.59,1:03:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with it. So you can say\Nit's in the name of the highest
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.20,1:03:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,good that my company\Nby this other little corporation
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.20,1:03:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that we expand,\Nwe triple the size of our restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.29,1:03:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to go broke in the restaurant\Nworld is to be very successful and then
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.68,1:03:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,double it, double the size of the restaurant.\NHave you ever seen
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.68,1:03:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a little thriving Chinese restaurant,\Nyou know, there's steam all over,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.68,1:03:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Italian restaurant, you know,\Nyou can see the chef there with the spaghetti
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.68,1:04:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's a waiting line out there\Nso they're gonna double and triple it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.68,1:04:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so they close for six\Nweeks, reopen,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.03,1:04:10.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and it goes bankrupt.\NIn Sedona it happens all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.03,1:04:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, 15, 20 of them I can think of.\NThe energy of this change.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.92,1:04:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if I were him\NI would say in the name of the highest good
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.08,1:04:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that I double the size of this restaurant\Nand you're probably gonna know. Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.08,1:04:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's the ambiance that's pulling the people\Nand if you double it and make it luxurious
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.08,1:04:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you've lost what they're there for.\NYou know, I can remember
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.33,1:04:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Gaslight\NDistrict, you know, a very
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.33,1:04:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,popular tavern, you know, very\Npopular, everybody goes there.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.33,1:04:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's very cool and hip, you know,\Nto hang out there near the gas
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.65,1:04:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,gasworks. So somebody\Nbuys it and decides they're gonna clean it up.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.65,1:04:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They close the\Nplace for six weeks,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.65,1:04:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,clean it all up, and now nobody goes there.\NBecause the energy
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.65,1:05:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,is all there. I remember the Electric Circus\Nback east in New York.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.65,1:05:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The Electric Circus was one of the first psychedelic\Nnightclubs.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.78,1:05:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And rock music, it was very avant-garde.\NAnd the cool and the hip went there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.78,1:05:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And there was a waiting line outside.\NSo they closed it, and of course
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.78,1:05:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,after a couple of years, Andy\NWarhol, the whole group used to hang out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.84,1:05:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So they closed it and expanded it.\NAnd what had been
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.29,1:05:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,really sorta funky\Nwas now like a white
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.68,1:05:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,alabaster and curved walls.\NReally weird.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.68,1:05:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,People went\Nback there, the acoustics were horrible
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.68,1:05:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because it bounced off these curved walls.\NAnd it went flat broke. Nobody went
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.68,1:05:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,there anymore. But when it was all jammed\Nup and funky looking,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.68,1:05:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,it was\Nwhere everybody went, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.87,1:05:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So the thing\Nto do then is you can pose anything
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.92,1:05:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that you would consider personal,\Nbut pose it in a way that is not
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.92,1:05:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,just like you're gonna vote.\NThe way to vote is
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.34,1:06:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,not, I'm always amazed when I hear people\Ncome on television, they say,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.34,1:06:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,they're gonna vote for so-and-so because he's gonna\Nvote for higher wages for truck drivers.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.34,1:06:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the guy's a truck driver.\NI never hear anybody say, I'm gonna vote for so-and-so
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.10,1:06:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because I think it's the best for the country.\NYou know, you could say,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.10,1:06:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,which would\Nserve the best interest of
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.10,1:06:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,mankind or the country\Ninstead of just me? I mean, it seems
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.23,1:06:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to me you would vote for whoever you think is gonna be\Nthe best for the country.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.23,1:06:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And last night on TV, they were saying,\Nyou know, the guy makes pickles and he's gonna vote for
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.23,1:06:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,whoever pays more to pickle\Nmakers than packers or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.23,1:06:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's so completely\Nself-interested. I don't believe
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.23,1:06:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,this that people think in such a petty way.\NYou know, only me, me, me.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.23,1:06:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's the ego,\Negocentricity, and
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.23,1:06:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it looks to gain.\NYou see, it's always looking, it's demanding
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.23,1:06:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and it looks to gain.\NAnd, alright,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.12,1:07:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,so that's, we could spend a whole\Nlecture on this, and we used to spend a whole lecture
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.12,1:07:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,on just going over the\Nscale of consciousness and the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.12,1:07:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,incredible implications.\NIn the United States of
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.05,1:07:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,America,\Nwell, let's go to the next slide. We'll get
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.11,1:07:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,there. Anyway, let's go to the next slide.\NWell, we'll go to that after a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.17,1:07:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In the\Nworld, then, 15%
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.17,1:07:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of the world's population\Ncalibrates over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.52,1:07:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,15%.\NIf you drop yourself off in the world
Dialogue: 0,1:07:35.47,1:07:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with a parachute, the chances\Nare, 85%,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.50,1:07:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,that the people around you will be\Nnon-integrists. As you'll see
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.20,1:07:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,later, you're safer with Coco,\Nthe gorilla,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.20,1:07:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,than you are\Nin the United States.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.20,1:07:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, only 49%\Nof the people calibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.20,1:08:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200.\NIn the United States, which calibrates overall at
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.33,1:08:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,421, 51%\Nof the people calibrate over 200
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.33,1:08:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and are integrists.\NSo that's a very interesting development.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.49,1:08:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We, on the scale of\Nconsciousness, we went up to 600
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.59,1:08:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,because\Nthere are only a half a dozen people on the planet
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.59,1:08:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,at any time, at this time,\Nthat calibrate over 600. So, it's not
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.59,1:08:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,too useful.\NWe do use it in
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.59,1:08:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrating spiritual teachers throughout\Nhistory. They're the only ones that go over 600.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.59,1:08:32.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Nisargadatta Maharaj,\Nvarious people like that, up to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.78,1:08:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nup to 600 is really all
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.88,1:08:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of it. At 600,\Nthe linear dissolves
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.88,1:08:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,into the non-linear.\NAnd 50% of the
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.97,1:08:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,time, when people hit level 600,\Nthey leave. They leave
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.07,1:08:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,just because.\NBecause,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.07,1:08:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,well,\Nthey leave and
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.07,1:09:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,they just topple over.\NAt that level, everything, you don't
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.23,1:09:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,need anything.\NAnd everybody around you thinks you need something, but
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.22,1:09:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that's because they want to keep the body going,\Nwhich is their problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.15,1:09:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So, they feed it and make sure you wash it\Nand all kinds of strange things.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.18,1:09:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So, 600 and up, you're at the mercy\Nof the people around you.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.88,1:09:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember Ramana Maharshi,\NRamana Maharshi was
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.95,1:09:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,just an ordinary\Nreligious, ordinarily religious
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.95,1:09:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,person, not unduly.\NAnd then, in teenage
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.95,1:09:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere, I forget what age,\Nhe suddenly went into a different state
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.11,1:09:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and he fell down and died.\NHe felt himself die.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.11,1:09:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And he did die.\NAnd what
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.07,1:09:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,survived was his consciousness, which\Nremained silent for several
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.07,1:09:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,years. Anyway, he\Nwas bitten by all kinds
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.07,1:10:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,of insects, hadn't eaten in weeks, and\Nsome spiritually advanced
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.07,1:10:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,people discovered his condition\Nand saw to it that he ate
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.07,1:10:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and various things like that. And he did\Nnot even speak for two years.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.07,1:10:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is probably a good\Nidea.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.20,1:10:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the subjective\Nstates. So, we calibrated them even though
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.92,1:10:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,they're unusual. Historically, they're\Ncited all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:22.92,1:10:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Teachers of enlightenment, avatars,\Nuh,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.08,1:10:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,avatars in 1985.\NSo, these are the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:31.08,1:10:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,depictions of\Ndivinity, Brahma,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.08,1:10:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,uh,\Nand then archangels,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.17,1:10:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,who you gotta be careful of.\NArchangels calibrate about 50,000 and up.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.23,1:10:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've told the story\Nof my own personal evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:49.23,1:10:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,In the pits of hell,\Nin the pits of hell,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:53.36,1:10:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in the very bottom of hell,\Nof absolute blackness and forever despair,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.36,1:11:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,a voice arose\Nwithin that said,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.39,1:11:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,if there is a God,\NI ask him for help.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:05.68,1:11:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And then silence\Nand oblivion.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.74,1:11:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the explosion\Nof the wondrous state
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.00,1:11:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,which revealed divinity\Nas creation itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.03,1:11:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only as source, but as creation.\NAnd
Dialogue: 0,1:11:23.60,1:11:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,then the mind was like\Nshock silent in awe.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.14,1:11:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It is still silent in awe.\NSo, you gotta be careful
Dialogue: 0,1:11:32.33,1:11:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of archangels,\Nbecause I always pictured
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.29,1:11:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was a cruising archangel, see?\NAnd here's this idiot in the depths of hell,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.42,1:11:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,says, I ask him if there is a God.\NAnd he just glances over like,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.42,1:11:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,hmm, bang.\NArchangel, 50,000 and up.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.25,1:11:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you're talking about\Na logarithmic scale.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.25,1:12:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You can imagine what 50,000 is.\N10 times 10 times 10, 50,000 times
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.32,1:12:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the power is so infinite,\Nit's incomprehensible.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.32,1:12:08.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The power there is absolute.\NIt's because of the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:08.38,1:12:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,absoluteness of the power\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,1:12:13.15,1:12:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the unmanifest\Nbecomes manifest.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.04,1:12:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The creation,\Nwhich is merely a thought,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:22.14,1:12:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,then begins to unfold.\NCreation and evolution are one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.52,1:12:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the way creation\Npresents itself
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.52,1:12:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,seems sequential\Nand evolutionary.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.52,1:12:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What's not evolutionary\Nwhat's evolutionary
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.38,1:12:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is the witness.\NWhat is sequential is the witnessing.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.89,1:12:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you witness evolution\Nand it seems to be sequential,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.89,1:12:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you think evolution is sequential.\NIt's a total oneness.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.89,1:12:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It is neither sequential\Nnor does it even occur within time,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.02,1:13:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the programming\Nwhich the mind projects on the phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.34,1:13:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go away from that.\NThe calibrated levels of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.76,1:13:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,this is their equivalent\Nin microwatts.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.79,1:13:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So as you see,\Nbelow level,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.79,1:13:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness level 200,\Nthe power is limited,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.79,1:13:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,very limited.\NAnd then as your consciousness advances,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.79,1:13:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,your power becomes extraordinary.\NOkay, so we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:25.79,1:13:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the equivalent in microwatts.\N85% of the world lives
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.11,1:13:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,below consciousness level 200.\NSo the great volume
Dialogue: 0,1:13:34.11,1:13:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of humanity then\Nis below
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.11,1:13:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,level 200.\NWhy do you get
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.84,1:13:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is not a celestial realm?\NYes, Walmart has
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.16,1:13:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,vaults. I agree.\NGovernment officials
Dialogue: 0,1:13:54.59,1:13:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,are human. Yeah.\NTrue.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.20,1:14:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is not a celestial realm\Nwhere no such phenomena occur.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:03.20,1:14:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.\NWhy doesn't mankind self-destruct?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.36,1:14:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of the exponential power.\NThe 15%
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.36,1:14:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,have so much power\Nthat they totally counterbalance
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.36,1:14:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,95%.\NThe power, the 15%.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.73,1:14:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So the kindly, loving, forgiving\Nthoughts that you have,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.56,1:14:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not conscious of it.\NBut that is counterbalancing
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.56,1:14:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,980 people\Nthinking of suicide
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.40,1:14:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,who suddenly at the last moment\Nthink, oh,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.75,1:14:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe I'll give it another try.\NIt's because of the presence
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.78,1:14:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of the infinite power\Nof this field.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.78,1:14:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And as a consequence\Nof what they are,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.26,1:14:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,what they have become,\Ncounterbalances.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.74,1:15:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what they do,\Npeople think, well, we'll have a peace parade.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.51,1:15:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It's what you have become\Nthat is the power
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.51,1:15:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that counterbalances.\NWhat you do is relatively
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.63,1:15:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,irrelevant.\NWhat you do is only a consequence
Dialogue: 0,1:15:13.66,1:15:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,of what you have become anyway.\NWhat you have become.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.66,1:15:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So consciousness is like a light bulb\Nand the higher the level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.66,1:15:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the more intense the light\Nthat it shines out.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.92,1:15:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The more intense the light that it shines out.\NSo what's the next one?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.36,1:15:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we got there already.\NWhat happened to the evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.11,1:15:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness over time?\NThe time graph.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.11,1:15:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that was supposed to be next.\NWe can live without it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.20,1:15:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NWell, we got a little bit out of step.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.84,1:15:58.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This was sent by a man named,\Nit's easy to remember his name.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.84,1:16:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,An engineering student.\NThis suddenly appeared in the mail.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.22,1:16:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as the previous graph.\NHis name is Daniel Lyons.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.22,1:16:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that an easy one to remember?\NI always think of Daniel
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.57,1:16:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and the lion's den.\NThis guy's name is Daniel Lyons.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.57,1:16:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is an adorable name.\NAnd he sent this to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.57,1:16:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a mathematician,\Nan engineering student.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.57,1:16:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This is how much\Nevolutionary time
Dialogue: 0,1:16:32.99,1:16:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,has elapsed.\NAnd you see the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.99,1:16:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated level of consciousness.\NIt's only in the last flick of time
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.05,1:16:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that the calibrated\Nlevel of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.05,1:16:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is now up to\N207 or so.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.31,1:16:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It took this much\Nevolutionary time,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.50,1:16:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,eons and eons,\Nbefore it even moved off the carpet.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.72,1:17:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It barely got off the carpet\Nafter eons and eons
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.72,1:17:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,of time.\NNow it's
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.40,1:17:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,beginning to rise.\NPeople say, what do you think is the future of mankind?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.40,1:17:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, all I can do is look at this graph\Nand from this graph it looks like
Dialogue: 0,1:17:16.40,1:17:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the consciousness of mankind\Nis about to catapult ahead.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.72,1:17:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, learning kinesiology\Nand how to tell truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.72,1:17:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that we lecture about\Nis a consequence of this.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.16,1:17:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a consequence of the evolution of consciousness\Nthat we're now able to tell truth from falsehood
Dialogue: 0,1:17:33.16,1:17:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and do so in a second\Nabout anything, anywhere in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:37.16,1:17:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Or history.\NSo long as the question is
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.12,1:17:46.12,Default,,0,0,0,,integrous and the people asking it are integrous.\NSo here's where we are
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.12,1:17:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and you could\Npretty much predict.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.12,1:17:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The nature of consciousness itself\Nis to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:54.12,1:17:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So now we'll move to the next slide.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.40,1:18:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we gotta go backwards to evolutionary time.\NI got those backwards.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.40,1:18:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, okay, that's right.\NIt's my fault
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.40,1:18:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because I changed all these charts\Nyesterday and
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.40,1:18:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Betty was trying to keep up with it.\NHow does this start here?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.23,1:18:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes.\NI have all kinds of pointers
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.23,1:18:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course they're all home.\NSo I'll be the pointer.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.75,1:18:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The beginning of time.\NThe beginning of the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.07,1:18:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,How did consciousness evolve?\NThis is critical
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.39,1:18:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand from a spiritual\Nviewpoint. I'll tell you why.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.39,1:18:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego.\NOh, look at that. Right out of the mystical
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.39,1:18:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,wonderment of the universe.\NHow did I do that, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.39,1:19:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Intention manifests\Nwhen the conditions are appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.76,1:19:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,\Nhow he and I and the pointer and the audience
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.76,1:19:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,are all one concordance.\NIt's all one concordance
Dialogue: 0,1:19:16.76,1:19:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course this evolves\Nwhen it's needed.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.63,1:19:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This is crucial to understand.\NIt's not academic at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.23,1:19:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-hatred, guilt, all this stuff\Nthat comes about from egocentricity.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.23,1:19:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Hating yourself,\Nshame, guilt, all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.23,1:19:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all a response\Nto our perceptions,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:42.44,1:19:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritually evolved people,\Nour perception of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.44,1:19:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you understand the\Nevolution of the ego and its core,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.44,1:19:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the essence of it, you stop feeling guilty\Nabout it. Now you can
Dialogue: 0,1:19:55.72,1:20:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,transcend it.\NThe first signs of life, the unmanifest
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.58,1:20:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes manifest.\NSo the universe evolves
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.58,1:20:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,as a physicality.\NWhat is to become planet Earth
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.61,1:20:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is liquid lava,\Nno, just energy flying around
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.61,1:20:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,which condenses itself\Nbecause E equals MC squared
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.61,1:20:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,to the potential\Nfor
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.68,1:20:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you call\Nour galaxy and then
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.67,1:20:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a little glob of it spins out\Nof these hot gases and it condenses
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.67,1:20:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to lava. And over the\Neons this then cools
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.70,1:20:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,off enough to develop a crust\Non it that could sustain
Dialogue: 0,1:20:39.12,1:20:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,life. The interaction\Nof consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:43.34,1:20:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the interaction of the\Ninfinite power of the unmanifest
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.34,1:20:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when it interacts\Nwith matter is that it can
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.34,1:20:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,spawn the emergence of life.\NSo the source of life
Dialogue: 0,1:20:55.37,1:20:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,is consciousness.\NThe source of life is
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.56,1:21:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,non-physical. The source\Nof life is
Dialogue: 0,1:21:05.39,1:21:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the impact of consciousness\Non material when
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.39,1:21:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions are\Nappropriate for this.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:13.87,1:21:18.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That takes care of the mechanistic reductionist.\NLife does not
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.92,1:21:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,arise from non-life.\NYou see the imbecility of such
Dialogue: 0,1:21:23.08,1:21:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,a proposition. That's what's\Ncalled mixing paradigms.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.08,1:21:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Mixing levels of abstraction.\NViolating the Kantian
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.15,1:21:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,categories. It's\Ndumb.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.43,1:21:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Life has completely\Ndifferent qualities from non-life.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.81,1:21:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The mundane mechanical\Nchemical
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.68,1:21:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot create something of a\Ntotally different level of
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.68,1:21:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,being, existence, paradigm.\NIt's a violation even within
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.68,1:21:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the Newtonian world of\Nlogic. What happened to, oh my
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.68,1:22:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,god, I said\Nsomething wrong, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.68,1:22:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I say somebody\Nwas feeling blue or what happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.80,1:22:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, without\Nthat, folks,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.04,1:22:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we had a good prognosis for a\Nwhile, but I've got the
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.67,1:22:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,transparency with me if the worst\Ncomes to worst.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.99,1:22:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,She can play with that. We'll get it back then.\NOh my.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.24,1:22:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the computer world, I stay away\Nfrom it as far as I can.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:33.24,1:22:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a trap. Once it gets you by\Nthe ankle, you can't get
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.24,1:22:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,loose on it.\NAlright, so the evolution of
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.76,1:22:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,life then. Somewhere back in\Ninfinite time.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.30,1:22:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Unmanifest as\Nthe power of
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.46,1:22:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself, the infinite field of\Nconsciousness, interacted
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.46,1:22:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,with material matter\Nand activated
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.46,1:23:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of life.\NNow, life as it first
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.68,1:23:06.68,Default,,0,0,0,,appeared on this crusty\Nplanet
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.68,1:23:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,did not emerge\Nunder favorable conditions.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.68,1:23:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, if you landed\Non Mars, your survival
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.68,1:23:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,would be dependent on\Ngetting energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.68,1:23:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So life is born\Nwithout the source of energy
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.83,1:23:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,within it, it has to get it.\NSo the first organism that arose
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.83,1:23:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,was the bacteria.\NBacteria calibrate as one.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.83,1:23:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That moved on to\Nprotozoa, calibrate
Dialogue: 0,1:23:36.92,1:23:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as three. Then on into\Nthe insect world.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:40.92,1:23:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can see the basic quality of life\Nis that
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.92,1:23:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the organism has to go\Noutside of itself for the energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:48.92,1:23:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And our\Nbad karma as humans
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.05,1:23:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is that we're not born green.\NIf we're
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.63,1:24:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we need chlorophyll instead of skin.\NWhen I get back there to the other side
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.63,1:24:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gonna tell them too.\NNext time you do it,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:07.64,1:24:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,boss, how about making us green, okay?\NIf you're green,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:14.46,1:24:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need a job, you don't need money,\Nyou don't have to go to work.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.91,1:24:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You just walk around being who you are.\NHappily,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.36,1:24:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,your green energy\Ncreates energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.36,1:24:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in the animal world\Nunfortunately,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.64,1:24:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to get.\NSo the core of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:24:35.77,1:24:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is self-interest.\NThe core of the ego
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.87,1:24:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is get.\NAnd you see the appeal to the voters
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.87,1:24:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,today is based on the same\Nget. It's a solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,1:24:47.87,1:24:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,energy. Why?\NBecause the organism
Dialogue: 0,1:24:51.96,1:24:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is born, it does not\Nhave within itself
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.96,1:24:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity to create energy.\NSo the animal kingdom
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.96,1:25:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,has to get it from somewhere.\NAnd the easiest way is
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.96,1:25:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to eat it.\NSo we're born to eat.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.12,1:25:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Without eating you die.\NSo if you were green
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.22,1:25:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you wouldn't have to eat.\NYou see what a break that would be?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.73,1:25:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's all go together.\NNext time we'll come back green
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.73,1:25:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,in a different place.\NYou don't have to go to work.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.73,1:25:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to save up money.\NWhat good would money be?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.88,1:25:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So the core of the ego then\Nconsciousness level below 200
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.88,1:25:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is get. Selfishness.\NSelf-centeredness.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.88,1:25:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is\Noh goody.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.65,1:25:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the core\Nof your animal.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.75,1:25:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside of you is an animal.\NAnd here's how the animal grew.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.42,1:25:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at time.\NRemember that thing about time?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:57.42,1:26:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It did nothing forever.\NAnd I just recently jumped up.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:01.42,1:26:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So these ages are so old\NI can't pronounce all these words.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.42,1:26:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Trillions and quadrillions\Nof rock ages
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.64,1:26:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and things.\NBacteria at one.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.18,1:26:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,In vertebrates.\NThen you get scorpions, snails,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.18,1:26:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,fish, amphibians,\Nreptiles.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.28,1:26:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally you get up to the dinosaurs.\NDinosaurs calibrate at 60.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.04,1:26:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's pretty good.\NWorld leaders in every day's headlines.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.54,1:26:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to hold somebody in line.\NHe calibrates over 60.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.91,1:27:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NIt's been loud, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.04,1:27:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does he calibrate lower than a dinosaur?\NBecause the dinosaur
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.64,1:27:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is innocent.\NIt eats the living
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.64,1:27:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because it has to\Nfor its own survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.76,1:27:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So the dinosaur's intention\Nis innocent.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.01,1:27:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The dinosaur's intention\Nis merely to eat.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.00,1:27:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And something below 60 then\Nwould have to be a pretty negative intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:29.00,1:27:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, that's just an\Naccidental thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:33.42,1:27:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we have the reptiles.\NAnd here we have the
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.42,1:27:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,higher dinosaurs.\NHere we have modern mammals.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.42,1:27:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And the rise and dominance\Nof man. So here you see
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.35,1:27:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,how consciousness\Nevolved protoplasmically
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.64,1:27:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as needing.\NNeedful.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:54.67,1:27:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore you don't have to feel guilty.\NThat your ego
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.67,1:28:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is greedy.\NOf course it's greedy.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.67,1:28:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't greedy you wouldn't be here.\NWe owe our survival to the animal within us.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:07.66,1:28:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And I call the\Nanimal in me ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.66,1:28:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego.\NNow we know that ego hates anybody
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.66,1:28:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,who cuts in on traffic\Nand that they should die.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.09,1:28:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows that the voters\Nwho are going to vote wrongly
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.18,1:28:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,deserve what they get\Nbecause they're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.80,1:28:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore\Nto win it's okay to lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:40.89,1:28:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to lie to win.\NBecause he thinks survival
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.89,1:28:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on winning and getting and gaining\Nand have power over others.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.89,1:28:53.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Why anybody would\Nwant power over others is totally beyond me.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.46,1:29:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,To control other people, force them to think\Nthe way you think.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.94,1:29:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the temptation came\Nbecause it was of an extremely high
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.94,1:29:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,space beyond mind and\Nthinkingness and mentalization
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.58,1:29:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,there was really nothing left\Nother than the source of life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.58,1:29:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And there came to me\Nso that I understood
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.73,1:29:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,what came to Jesus Christ.\NThere comes to you in the silence
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.96,1:29:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a knowingness.\NThere's a knowingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:26.96,1:29:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a silent transmission.\NIt's like what? Telepathic I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:30.96,1:29:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Telepathic.\NNow that you know that you
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.27,1:29:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,have transcended karma\Nnow that you know you're not answering
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.27,1:29:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the answer bolt.\NThat there is no God who will
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.27,1:29:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,punish you.\NThere is no consequences for all actions.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.27,1:29:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All power is yours.\NOwn it.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:52.59,1:29:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was\NI saw what Christ said there
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.91,1:30:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,because there aren't too many people\Nat that high pass.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.13,1:30:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And he turned it down.\NAnd a few others I saw were there
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.40,1:30:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,turned it down.\NAnd happily I saw
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.95,1:30:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,who would want power over others.\NAnd so I turned it down.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.95,1:30:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Own it.\NAnd all power is yours.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.84,1:30:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Own it and all power is yours.\NBecause there is no payment.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.84,1:30:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You're even beyond love.\NEven beyond love.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.84,1:30:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So you would not even be constrained\Nby love.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.84,1:30:36.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You could put all the poor widows\Nout of your apartment house
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.84,1:30:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and double the rent.\NAnd if they starved to death
Dialogue: 0,1:30:41.23,1:30:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because you no longer have love for others\Nyou're beyond love.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.23,1:30:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond love is an error\Nbecause love is one of the attributes
Dialogue: 0,1:30:50.09,1:30:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,of God.\NAnd a teaching that
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.12,1:30:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,negates love as\Nonly a manipulation
Dialogue: 0,1:30:58.12,1:31:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,or wanting other people's approval\Nis a very serious
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.12,1:31:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,very serious error.\N180 serious error.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.51,1:31:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is one of the qualities of divinity.\NSo when you look at yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:31:11.72,1:31:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you can say\Nwhat do I want with power over others?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.72,1:31:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,What a drag it would be wouldn't it?\NWouldn't it be a drag?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:20.24,1:31:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That power over others\Ncontrol how they think
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.24,1:31:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and what they believe and all that.\NSo anyway
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.12,1:31:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,we see the rise and dominance of man\Nand we see
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.41,1:31:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and we saw from that previous chart\Nthat it's only about now.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:38.41,1:31:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay so move on to the next slide.\NWhat say?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.55,1:31:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,She thinks for me, thank God.\NLet's go back, let's go to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.89,1:31:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay and\Nvery interestingly
Dialogue: 0,1:31:54.89,1:31:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,this is one of my favorite slides\Nand after you've seen this slide
Dialogue: 0,1:31:58.89,1:32:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and comprehend it\Nit will eliminate guilt forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:02.89,1:32:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Guilt, shame,\Nhatred
Dialogue: 0,1:32:06.89,1:32:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you get rid of it all now forever.\NBecause once you understand
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.89,1:32:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,the core of the narcissist\Nis the ego that you were born with.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.89,1:32:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You were born with an animal brain\Nthat's your hardware.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:18.89,1:32:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmically you come in with software\Nbut that software now has to play on this hardware.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.89,1:32:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You're stuck with biologic hardware of an animal folks.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.44,1:32:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We own our animal.\NThe way we disappeared is
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.75,1:32:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we stopped making an enemy of them\Nand we say yeah I've got an animal nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.96,1:32:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So here we see the protozoa.\NWe see
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.96,1:32:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,oh I've got a pointer now.\NAnd look
Dialogue: 0,1:32:46.32,1:32:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,this is really fun.\NYou see how they all come up here?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.32,1:32:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Crustaceans, insects,\Ngrasshoppers. Here's grasshoppers.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.38,1:32:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not too smart, huh?\NBut they're still around.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:58.51,1:33:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Reptiles,\Nsnakes, alligators.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:04.83,1:33:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know. I don't understand people\Nwho play with alligators.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.86,1:33:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just macho that you can grab an alligator\Nget your picture taken.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.86,1:33:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to see them grab a dinosaur though.\NLet's see you do that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.21,1:33:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Or a Komodo dragon.\NAnd we see whales
Dialogue: 0,1:33:21.31,1:33:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and dolphins,\Nmigratory birds, birds of prey,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.31,1:33:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,rhinoceros,\Nsongbirds, doves.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:29.37,1:33:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And polar bear,\Nwater buffalo. Water buffalo are
Dialogue: 0,1:33:33.50,1:33:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,very dangerous. Water buffalo\Nwill be staying there and then just suddenly for no reason
Dialogue: 0,1:33:37.50,1:33:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,he'll charge you.\NBut he's not as dangerous as the hippopotamus.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.46,1:33:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And I always tell people about the hippopotamus.\NKills more humans than any other
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.46,1:33:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,wild animal. Do not hang\Nout with hippopotamus if you get nothing else
Dialogue: 0,1:33:50.81,1:33:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,out of this lecture.\NYou see these idiots in canoes
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.68,1:33:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,are hanging out with hippopotamus.\NFinally he says
Dialogue: 0,1:33:59.68,1:34:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Four people plus a canoe\Ngo down his goal.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:04.67,1:34:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Just do not hang out.\NYou see there's people that haven't even gotten
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.67,1:34:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that far. Do not hang out\Nwith hippopotamus.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:15.52,1:34:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not lay down on the railroad track.\NYou know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:22.30,1:34:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you see the emergence of the grazers.\NAnd much to our surprise when we calibrated these
Dialogue: 0,1:34:26.30,1:34:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw suddenly we had\Ngone over consciousness level 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.30,1:34:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the critical level\Nin the human. And wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.30,1:34:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is. The critical level\Ncharacteristic difference between
Dialogue: 0,1:34:38.30,1:34:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,animals below 200 and animals\Nover 200. Below
Dialogue: 0,1:34:42.30,1:34:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,200 they live at the price of the life\Nof others. They have
Dialogue: 0,1:34:46.30,1:34:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to eat and kill\Nin order to live. And now
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.30,1:34:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,at 200 suddenly you become benign.\NJust like the human dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:54.30,1:34:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200 people are dangerous.\NThey're not safe till
Dialogue: 0,1:34:58.56,1:35:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,they're 200 and over.\NAnd the animal kingdom, you see the same
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.23,1:35:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,phenomena. Isn't that curious?\NConsciousness level 200
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.23,1:35:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,then differentiates. That\Nwhich is dangerous
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.42,1:35:15.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which is benign.\NSo the animal once it reaches
Dialogue: 0,1:35:15.42,1:35:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,200 becomes a grazer.\NIt eats grass. It doesn't kill
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.42,1:35:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,anybody. It doesn't tear them to pieces.\NAnd
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.42,1:35:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you see they'll defend themselves\Nlike an elephant. You get up
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.42,1:35:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to cats at 240. Family\Ncat 245. So when
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.42,1:35:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you adopt a pet\Njust their being around you
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.42,1:35:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,advances their consciousness 5\Nsometimes even 10 points.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.42,1:35:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Family dog you see.\NMonkeys, gorillas, chimpanzees.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.42,1:35:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And here's\Nan African Grey.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:49.40,1:35:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Alex. Alex\Nis Broccoli's
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.66,1:35:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,ideal.\NYou keep listening
Dialogue: 0,1:35:58.81,1:36:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty soon you'll be smart as Alex.\NYou'll be smart
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.13,1:36:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,as Alex.\NOur Grey is named Broccoli.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.13,1:36:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've been calibrating Broccoli every couple of months.\NCoco. We all know
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.13,1:36:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Coco. Coco is\Nreally quite benign.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:15.13,1:36:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You're safer with Coco\Na gorilla than most
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.13,1:36:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of the people on the planet.\NCoco is at 405.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.29,1:36:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we see the\Nwonderment of these two pets.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.29,1:36:31.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that the cat's purr\Ncalibrates at
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.29,1:36:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,500 and the dog's wagging tail\Ncalibrates at 500.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.29,1:36:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,500 is love.\NSo the dog's wagging tail
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.29,1:36:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the cat's purr\Nis reflecting the
Dialogue: 0,1:36:43.29,1:36:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,energy of love.\NAnd I'll just tell the last story when we were in Toronto
Dialogue: 0,1:36:47.29,1:36:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we'll take a break.\NAnd when we were in Toronto
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.29,1:36:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,on the front page of the paper\Nthe day we gave the lecture
Dialogue: 0,1:36:55.29,1:36:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,was the story of a dog named Elvis.\NAnd Elvis, there was a man in the park
Dialogue: 0,1:36:59.29,1:37:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,who had\N6,000 rounds of ammo
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.29,1:37:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and high powered rifles\Nand he was like the famous
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.29,1:37:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,killers that hit the newsreel\Ngonna mow down everybody, kill everybody
Dialogue: 0,1:37:11.29,1:37:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and then kill himself.\NHe would not give up his weapons.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.52,1:37:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He would not give up his weapons.\NAll of a sudden
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.06,1:37:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Elvis, this dog\Nran across with a
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.06,1:37:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,frisbee in his mouth\Nand jumped up and wanted this
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.06,1:37:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,guy to play.\NAnd this guy suddenly came to his senses
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.06,1:37:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly said, what the hell am I doing?\NAnd dropped his
Dialogue: 0,1:37:36.06,1:37:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,rifle and surrendered to the\Nofficials and I guess he's now in treatment.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.06,1:37:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But see Elvis came up\Nwith an energy fuel to 500
Dialogue: 0,1:37:44.06,1:37:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,so his wagging tail\Nhis 500
Dialogue: 0,1:37:48.06,1:37:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,hit this man's dementia\Nand the man became sane.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:52.06,1:37:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing.\NThe healing power of love which we know
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.06,1:38:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,experientially\Nin therapeutics.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:00.22,1:38:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that people who have dogs and cats\Nor pets and love them
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.22,1:38:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,live longer, have lower blood pressure\Nhave fewer heart attacks, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.22,1:38:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean that you can't get out of here\Nbut they'll
Dialogue: 0,1:38:12.22,1:38:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll make the way\Nwaiting time more pleasant.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.22,1:38:20.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Sitting on the park bench\Nwaiting to leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.22,1:38:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You can have your kitty purring in your lap\Nand when you leave.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.22,1:38:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's time to leave the planet\Nall I want is the cat and the kitty
Dialogue: 0,1:38:28.22,1:38:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and the surrounding\Nbeing surrounded by love.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:32.22,1:38:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Love tends to bring\Nlove to oneself. So loving people
Dialogue: 0,1:38:36.22,1:38:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I think tend to have loving pets.\NSo we're going to take a break for how long?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.22,1:38:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Fifteen minutes.\NFifteen minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.25,1:38:54.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Thank you so much.\NWhere's the sound person?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:54.70,1:38:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Sound person.\NSound person.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.95,1:39:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the sound person?\NWe know that a fifteen minute break
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.21,1:39:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,always takes half an hour.\NThat's why we give you fifteen minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.21,1:39:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If we gave you half an hour\Nit would take forty-five.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:19.56,1:39:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in all the excitement here\NI forgot what today's lecture was about.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:26.54,1:39:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But now I remember.\NToday's lecture is called
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.72,1:39:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We said the human mind\Ncannot move faster than
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.12,1:39:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,one ten-thousandth of a second.\NTherefore, how are you going to
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.19,1:39:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,discover\Nthis field here?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:46.41,1:39:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When\Nin early life, teenage or whatever it was
Dialogue: 0,1:39:54.19,1:39:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I caught the\Nmind claiming credit
Dialogue: 0,1:39:59.02,1:40:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,for saving the life of the rabbit.\NIt wasn't the mind that did that.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.31,1:40:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't the mind that did that.\NIt was the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:08.14,1:40:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The field.\NThat's where the first mind arises.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:12.88,1:40:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The witness observer.\NPeople want to know how to become enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:18.03,1:40:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell them.\NStop identifying with content
Dialogue: 0,1:40:22.51,1:40:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and identify with the field.\NBecause meditation is something that
Dialogue: 0,1:40:26.73,1:40:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to be somewhat artificial.\NIt's not what you do in everyday life.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:31.05,1:40:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people go someplace\Nand pay money to learn it
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.05,1:40:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and spend three weeks learning it.\NAnd you're very enthused about meditation.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.43,1:40:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So you do it.\NI did it myself for an hour in the morning
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.84,1:40:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and night for many years.\NAnd then what happens is
Dialogue: 0,1:40:49.07,1:40:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,your life gets to be too busy.\NAnd so now you do it for half an hour
Dialogue: 0,1:40:53.07,1:40:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you skip Monday morning\Nand then Thursday night you forget it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:57.07,1:41:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And within six months you've given up meditation.\NThen you go to a retreat
Dialogue: 0,1:41:02.89,1:41:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and you do it again for a week.\NSo it's not something that you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:07.88,1:41:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's something\Nin addition
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.36,1:41:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,compartmentalized.\NI think I'll go and meditate now.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.46,1:41:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It means you've got to leave everything.\NGet off the TV.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.49,1:41:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell the dog\Ngo lay down.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:25.16,1:41:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to go to some special place.\NGet a special mat.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.42,1:41:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Special perfume, incense,\Nall kinds of images of divine figures.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.42,1:41:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You go into this state.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:38.92,1:41:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And then when you\Nstand up and walk around
Dialogue: 0,1:41:43.21,1:41:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,back.\NYou're right back to where you were.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.52,1:41:57.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness is advanced by\Nidentifying with the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.71,1:42:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Not with the content of the field\Nbut with the field itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:01.84,1:42:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the witness observer.\NSee.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:05.93,1:42:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is literal and linear\Nand it's good for
Dialogue: 0,1:42:11.21,1:42:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,figuring out what all the controls are\Nin the car, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:15.69,1:42:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a new Chevy\Nand it's got 100 controls.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:19.69,1:42:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,100 controls.\NAt my age that's a nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:24.84,1:42:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the on\Nor off?
Dialogue: 0,1:42:29.77,1:42:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Great.\NI'm going to go see these
Dialogue: 0,1:42:33.80,1:42:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and then see these playing when I'm driving.\NI would have run over the rabbit.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:38.38,1:42:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NWhen you drive
Dialogue: 0,1:42:44.33,1:42:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you trust the field, don't you?\NYou don't just trust what you're looking at
Dialogue: 0,1:42:48.36,1:42:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because this car is just coming in\Nfrom this side.
Dialogue: 0,1:42:52.36,1:42:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When you drive\Nyou tend to spread your consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:42:56.36,1:43:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and your awareness to the field.\NOr you better or you wouldn't be here today.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:00.36,1:43:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NYou're aware of the totality.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:09.61,1:43:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You're aware of your creative lifestyle\Nthan this one
Dialogue: 0,1:43:13.64,1:43:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in which\Nyou become aligned with the field
Dialogue: 0,1:43:20.52,1:43:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than the content of the field.\NAnd we'll get to a diagram about that later.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:24.81,1:43:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to be the field.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:29.04,1:43:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the field and the observer\Ndo not move within time.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:33.90,1:43:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind has to move from\Nthe particular to the particular
Dialogue: 0,1:43:38.32,1:43:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to the particular.\NIt's confined to the linear
Dialogue: 0,1:43:42.96,1:43:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so the mind goes from this word\Nto this picture in the paper
Dialogue: 0,1:43:46.96,1:43:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to this TV thing.\NSo the mind can only move
Dialogue: 0,1:43:51.18,1:43:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,can't move any faster than\None tenth of a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:55.24,1:43:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Flicks from this to this.\NThe field doesn't move
Dialogue: 0,1:43:59.76,1:44:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,from anything to anything.\NIf you become
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.95,1:44:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,one with the field\Nthe field automatically
Dialogue: 0,1:44:08.20,1:44:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,notices\Nthat the brake went on before.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:12.20,1:44:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind took credit.\NIt was the witness observing
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.56,1:44:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that discerned that.\NSo the witness observer
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.59,1:44:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,is faster than\None tenth of a second
Dialogue: 0,1:44:24.88,1:44:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is not on and off.\NIt doesn't move from this to that.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.88,1:44:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the totality\Nof the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.91,1:44:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the field that sees all three fish\Narise out of the sea at once.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:36.97,1:44:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If I look at this fish\Nand then this fish
Dialogue: 0,1:44:41.77,1:44:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't do it, right?\NIf you're one with the field
Dialogue: 0,1:44:47.76,1:44:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you see all three fish\Nsimultaneously of their own.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.76,1:44:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very obvious.\NYou don't have to attend lectures
Dialogue: 0,1:44:56.01,1:45:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to remind you what a flying fish knows.\NIt just is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:05.95,1:45:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't think\Noh I decided to leap out of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:09.95,1:45:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nature\Ndid that for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.17,1:45:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So the witness observer\Nand we'll get to a diagram
Dialogue: 0,1:45:18.24,1:45:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that explains that\Nis the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:23.16,1:45:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So I tend to emphasize contemplation\Nas a spiritual style.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:27.93,1:45:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,To be aware of the totality\Nof the field.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:33.34,1:45:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The current political thing is\Nit isn't what this one says
Dialogue: 0,1:45:37.53,1:45:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and what this one says.\NThat's what they all focus on.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:41.53,1:45:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's more the intention of the field.\NWhat's the intention of the field?
Dialogue: 0,1:45:45.53,1:45:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the intention of the people involved?\NWhat's the overall field
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.53,1:45:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're creating?\NThen you try to decide
Dialogue: 0,1:45:53.69,1:45:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which field is the best\Nfor the country.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.26,1:46:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw a TV\Nbeing interviewed saying
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.26,1:46:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,they're going to do what's best\Nfor the country.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:07.26,1:46:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,They're going to do what's best\Nfor us truck drivers
Dialogue: 0,1:46:11.26,1:46:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,or us plumbers\Nor us whatever
Dialogue: 0,1:46:15.45,1:46:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of the field.\NWhen you ask what
Dialogue: 0,1:46:19.90,1:46:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in the name of the highest good\Nso you would ask
Dialogue: 0,1:46:23.90,1:46:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,if you want to find out how to vote\Nin the name of the highest good
Dialogue: 0,1:46:27.90,1:46:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I would be best serving the highest good\Nappeals to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:32.00,1:46:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll go back to the slides.\NWe got as far as the dog's wagging tail
Dialogue: 0,1:46:38.86,1:46:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and Elvis.\NWe're going to go on to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.46,1:46:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the animal now\Nyou're born with
Dialogue: 0,1:46:48.46,1:46:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that's your physiology.\NThen on top of this animal brain
Dialogue: 0,1:46:57.45,1:47:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,evolves the prefrontal cortex.\NThe prefrontal cortex
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.76,1:47:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,does not replace\Nthe animal brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:07.47,1:47:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an add-on.\NNow you have the great
Dialogue: 0,1:47:12.11,1:47:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,difficulty of being a human being.\NIf I was St. Peter
Dialogue: 0,1:47:16.49,1:47:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say where have you been? Planet Earth?\NHave you been a human being? Yes. Pass.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:20.49,1:47:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause you're stuck with an animal brain
Dialogue: 0,1:47:24.49,1:47:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and a prefrontal cortex\Nwith spiritual awareness,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:28.49,1:47:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,honesty, integrity, answerability\Nand such things.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.49,1:47:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you've got\Na setup for conflict.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:37.93,1:47:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How to resolve the conflict then\Ntraditionally has been done
Dialogue: 0,1:47:41.93,1:47:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the down side, the gothic side\Nof traditional religion
Dialogue: 0,1:47:45.93,1:47:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,has been sin and guilt and penance, etc.\NAsh cloth,
Dialogue: 0,1:47:50.32,1:47:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,sackcloth and ashes.\NConsequently
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.88,1:47:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,few people have become enlightened in history.\NIt's an extreme rarity.
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.88,1:48:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Because\NGod is not at the bottom of the chart
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.88,1:48:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Calvary of the level of consciousness.\NGod is at the top.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.11,1:48:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Joy, happiness, forgiveness\NSo
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.11,1:48:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the first thing we learn is that\NGod is not at the bottom of the chart
Dialogue: 0,1:48:16.11,1:48:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,God is at the top of the chart.\NJoy, forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,1:48:20.11,1:48:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,love.\NWhat to do with the down side then?
Dialogue: 0,1:48:28.11,1:48:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,If you\Nvilify it, you set up a duality
Dialogue: 0,1:48:32.30,1:48:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the ego\Nbecomes your enemy. Your animal nature
Dialogue: 0,1:48:39.53,1:48:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,now becomes your enemy.\NAnd you have to do penance and say the rosary.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:45.55,1:48:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it gets angry\Nand it's the
Dialogue: 0,1:48:49.74,1:48:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,selfish, etc.\NThe way to eliminate a thing is to not
Dialogue: 0,1:48:54.19,1:48:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,resist it and to adopt it.\NYou adopt it.
Dialogue: 0,1:48:58.80,1:49:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My ego's name is\NEgo.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:02.80,1:49:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And I accept\Nthat ego is what it is
Dialogue: 0,1:49:07.05,1:49:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's my animal inheritance.\NInstead of vilifying it
Dialogue: 0,1:49:11.05,1:49:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I said of course you're selfish.\NOf course you want to win.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:15.34,1:49:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course people in traffic deserve to die.\NAnd the
Dialogue: 0,1:49:19.85,1:49:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,people who vote wrongly, we know who they are.\NDeserve what they get,
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.22,1:49:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,don't they?\NSo you just
Dialogue: 0,1:49:30.86,1:49:34.86,Default,,0,0,0,,assume that the ego is that way\Nand that everybody's ego is that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:41.68,1:49:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So you finally have a prefrontal\Ncortex. So as
Dialogue: 0,1:49:46.44,1:49:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness evolves,\Nit evolves from
Dialogue: 0,1:49:50.57,1:49:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the emotions of\Nthe negative emotions
Dialogue: 0,1:49:55.08,1:49:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,then it evolves to more positive\Nemotions.
Dialogue: 0,1:49:59.79,1:50:03.79,Default,,0,0,0,,At the very bottom it's pure animal emotion.\NAnd then it evolves
Dialogue: 0,1:50:03.79,1:50:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,from negative emotions, shame,\Nguilt, hatred, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:07.79,1:50:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,to positive emotions.\NEnthusiasm, commitment, reliability,
Dialogue: 0,1:50:11.79,1:50:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the traditional\Nvirtues of traditional America.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:15.79,1:50:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And eventually the\Nprefrontal cortex evolves to the point
Dialogue: 0,1:50:19.92,1:50:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,where it can think.\NMost people think they can think but that's
Dialogue: 0,1:50:24.17,1:50:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,an illusion. They're not thinking.\NThey think they're thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:29.07,1:50:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't really\Nthink until you get to consciousness level
Dialogue: 0,1:50:33.07,1:50:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,400, which excludes\Nmost voters.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.77,1:50:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Logic and\Nreason arose late
Dialogue: 0,1:50:47.77,1:50:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in the game.\NIt really hasn't made much
Dialogue: 0,1:50:52.06,1:50:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,progress since about\N350 BC.
Dialogue: 0,1:50:56.19,1:51:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In 350 BC, Aristotle,\NPlato, Socrates
Dialogue: 0,1:51:00.19,1:51:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty much, of course later refined\NKant and others.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:04.19,1:51:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But pretty much it was said\Nthe logic, the difference between rhetoric and
Dialogue: 0,1:51:08.19,1:51:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,logic, and the\Nparadigm of reality that
Dialogue: 0,1:51:12.22,1:51:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,dominates our current society.\NAmerican society calibrates at 421.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:16.22,1:51:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,400 is the level\Nof the intellect,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:21.02,1:51:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,reason, the prefrontal cortex,\Neducation, college.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:25.72,1:51:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So America calibrates higher than any country\Nin the world right now at 421.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:29.72,1:51:33.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So we celebrate\Ninventiveness, creativeness,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:33.72,1:51:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,intelligence,\Ngoing to college, learning,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:37.72,1:51:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,reading, becoming educated,\Nstaying up with current events,
Dialogue: 0,1:51:41.72,1:51:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,being informed.\NSo we emphasize
Dialogue: 0,1:51:45.72,1:51:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,intelligence.\NAnd out of it has come a great society.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:49.95,1:51:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,A great society.\NCapacity to reason and to think.
Dialogue: 0,1:51:55.29,1:51:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So let's, this is\Nthe world I grew up in. In childhood
Dialogue: 0,1:51:59.48,1:52:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,other people were playing stickball and\Nwrestling and all kinds of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:03.48,1:52:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And football and\Nall kinds of dangerous games.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:07.48,1:52:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't allow me on the football field.\NThe coach said, I don't want you on the football field
Dialogue: 0,1:52:11.48,1:52:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because your bones are just going to\Nget crunched. And so he wouldn't
Dialogue: 0,1:52:15.48,1:52:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,approve me for anything.\NThe worst day for me was field day
Dialogue: 0,1:52:21.80,1:52:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,when there was no classes and\Neverybody climbed ropes and did somersaults
Dialogue: 0,1:52:25.80,1:52:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and other nightmarish things.\NBecause I was into the great books
Dialogue: 0,1:52:30.48,1:52:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of the western world.\NWhich were assembled by
Dialogue: 0,1:52:35.21,1:52:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Mortimer Adler at the University of Chicago\Nin the 50s.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:39.21,1:52:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,These are the greatest thinkers the world has ever seen.\NThese are the people that set up the paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:52:43.21,1:52:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of America as it stands today.\NThe Constitution
Dialogue: 0,1:52:47.47,1:52:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,of the United States, which calibrates\Nat 710, the highest of any
Dialogue: 0,1:52:51.47,1:52:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world. 710.\N710. Extremely brilliant.
Dialogue: 0,1:52:59.04,1:53:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so terrific about the\NUnited States Constitution?
Dialogue: 0,1:53:03.23,1:53:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It says,\Nequality arises
Dialogue: 0,1:53:07.23,1:53:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,by virtue of the\Ndivinity of our creator.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:11.23,1:53:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The Americans political\Nrights arise out of
Dialogue: 0,1:53:16.25,1:53:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that out of the creator\Narose the rights of man.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:20.25,1:53:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Not by the vote.\NNot by secularism.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:24.25,1:53:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Not by one army winning over another.\NBut by virtue of the
Dialogue: 0,1:53:28.92,1:53:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity of our source.\NThat is what gives us
Dialogue: 0,1:53:33.12,1:53:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,freedom of religion\Nand freedom from religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:37.12,1:53:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,710.\NConstitution of the United States.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:41.12,1:53:45.47,Default,,0,0,0,,People that want to meddle with it,\Nwhen you calibrate them,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:45.47,1:53:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,are usually less than 200.\NChange the Constitution of the United States,
Dialogue: 0,1:53:49.47,1:53:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you calibrate that energy of that person,\Nyou usually find it's less than 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:53.47,1:53:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the sheer arrogance of it\Nis enough to put you below 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:53:57.47,1:54:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway,\Nhere you've got the greatest minds.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:01.47,1:54:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, while everybody else is playing stickball\Nand other violent games,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:06.01,1:54:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,sticking their fingers in each other's\Neyes and things,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:10.01,1:54:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sitting\Nwith a big book in front of me,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:14.01,1:54:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and I wore very thick glasses,\NI had trifocals and all.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:18.01,1:54:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's this skinny ectomorph,\Nyou know, a bookworm,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:22.01,1:54:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the mesomorphs\Nare out there whacking into each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:26.01,1:54:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I could never really get the pleasure of that.\NWhat is the pleasure of wrestling?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:30.01,1:54:34.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy's eyeballs are\Nin your point.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:34.01,1:54:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the kick out of that?\NYou know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:54:38.11,1:54:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I was fascinated with Aristotle\Nand Plato and
Dialogue: 0,1:54:42.56,1:54:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the aphorisms of Marcus Aurelius\Nand things like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:54:46.56,1:54:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see here's in the 400s\NThomas Aquinas and
Dialogue: 0,1:54:50.56,1:54:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Marcus Aurelius,\NSir Francis Bacon, Berkeley,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:54.56,1:54:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,all the great names of history.\NChaucer,
Dialogue: 0,1:54:58.56,1:55:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Darwin at 450.\NSo here you see the Newtonian paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:02.56,1:55:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Sir Isaac Newton?\NI think he's on here too, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,1:55:06.56,1:55:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the\Nidea of causality.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:11.55,1:55:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the problem with the human mind,\Nand I can't tell truth from falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:15.55,1:55:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,was delineated quite clearly\Nby Descartes.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:20.80,1:55:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem with the human mind\Nis its dualistic nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:25.21,1:55:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks\Nthat what res interna,
Dialogue: 0,1:55:29.85,1:55:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,res cogitans,\Nit thinks
Dialogue: 0,1:55:33.85,1:55:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that what it thinks\Nis what is out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:37.88,1:55:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It confuses res interna\Nwith res externa.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:42.08,1:55:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The reality of thinkingness\Nwith the reality of nature
Dialogue: 0,1:55:46.08,1:55:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is what the universe is.\NIf you follow what I'm saying
Dialogue: 0,1:55:51.71,1:55:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,you will see that\Nthe concept of causality
Dialogue: 0,1:55:55.87,1:55:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is res interna,\Nres cogitans.
Dialogue: 0,1:55:59.87,1:56:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a thinkingness.\NThat there is a this causing a that
Dialogue: 0,1:56:07.29,1:56:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,is a dualistic perception\Non the part of the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:13.12,1:56:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It now projects it\Ninto the world
Dialogue: 0,1:56:17.37,1:56:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and thinks causality is out there.\NIn thinking that, for one thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:24.67,1:56:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,when it comes to causality\Nit's violating a very
Dialogue: 0,1:56:29.12,1:56:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,basic principle of logic itself.\NBecause a thing follows another
Dialogue: 0,1:56:34.56,1:56:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn't mean\Nit's caused by that which preceded it.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:38.56,1:56:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the great illusion\Nwhich science itself falls into.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:42.84,1:56:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So science\Nis limited to the paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:56:46.84,1:56:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of about 450 to 460\Neven quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,1:56:52.54,1:56:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,To go beyond duality\Nyou then have to go into a different paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,1:56:56.54,1:57:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,a different paradigm.\NWithin the Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:57:00.89,1:57:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of causality.\NIf you're stuck with causality
Dialogue: 0,1:57:04.89,1:57:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to a spiritual student\Nyou're then stuck with the thought
Dialogue: 0,1:57:08.89,1:57:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that there is a personal separate I\Ncausing a that.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:17.47,1:57:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a personal I.\NIt's answerable, punishable,
Dialogue: 0,1:57:23.32,1:57:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,limited.\NAnd it causes that.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:28.99,1:57:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It decides that.\NThere's a separate personal self
Dialogue: 0,1:57:32.99,1:57:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,with a small s\Nthat is separate from the infinite oneness.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:37.12,1:57:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you constantly\Nidentify with the field
Dialogue: 0,1:57:43.77,1:57:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you will catch, the witness observer\Nwill see that everything is happening
Dialogue: 0,1:57:47.77,1:57:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,spontaneously.\NWe saw it happen spontaneously this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:57:52.12,1:57:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where things say\Nthings happen spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,1:57:56.12,1:58:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,as a result of intention.\NAudit came out of the audience, didn't it?
